"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1927036-paris-2024-olympic-rings-colours-mean-continents\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The2024 Paris Olympicsofficially kick off this week, with all eyes on the French capital for the sporting event of the summer.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10, \"end\": 15, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999993649664445, \"rank\": 6.350339079319545e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 76, \"end\": 82, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.873392264420672, \"rank\": 0.09995959087985172, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all eyes\", \"from\": 58, \"to\": 66}, {\"ngram\": \"the sporting event\", \"from\": 93, \"to\": 111}, {\"ngram\": \"the summer\", \"from\": 115, \"to\": 125}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But many of those peepers will have caught at least a glimpse of one of the most iconic symbols in sport without knowing what they mean.\", \"from\": 129, \"to\": 265, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those peepers\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 154}, {\"ngram\": \"at least a glimpse\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 190}, {\"ngram\": \"the most iconic symbols\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 224}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 228, \"to\": 233}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some have surmised the five interlaced rings have a meaning dating back to Ancient Greece, where the Summer Games were first born.\", \"from\": 267, \"to\": 397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 342, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9995799301733309, \"rank\": 0.00037742713982649766, \"text\": \"Ancient Greece\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the five interlaced rings\", \"from\": 286, \"to\": 311}, {\"ngram\": \"a meaning\", \"from\": 317, \"to\": 326}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Games\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 380}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, this was a myth perpetuated following a misplaced report by American authors Lynn and Gray Poole in the mid-20th century.\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 528, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 467, \"end\": 483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Authors\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"American authors\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Authors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Authors\"}, {\"begin\": 493, \"end\": 497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Edward_Gray\", \"score\": 0.9999999686349388, \"rank\": 3.037702782555895e-08, \"text\": \"Gray\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Edward_Gray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Edward_Gray\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a myth\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 422}, {\"ngram\": \"a misplaced report\", \"from\": 445, \"to\": 463}, {\"ngram\": \"the mid-20th century\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 527}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The origin of the rings is in fact far more modern and was conceived by French Baron Pierre de Coubertin.\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 602, \"end\": 608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.873392264420672, \"rank\": 0.09995959087985172, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 615, \"end\": 634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre de Coubertin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The origin\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 540}, {\"ngram\": \"the rings\", \"from\": 544, \"to\": 553}, {\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 564}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The historian - who served as the second president of the International Olympic Committee - first created the design in 1913 when the list of countries competing was considerably smaller.\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 823, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The historian\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 649}, {\"ngram\": \"the second president\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 686}, {\"ngram\": \"the International Olympic Committee\", \"from\": 690, \"to\": 725}, {\"ngram\": \"the design\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 752}, {\"ngram\": \"the list\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 774}, {\"ngram\": \"countries\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 787}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's widely believed the meaning of the rings and their five individual colours represents each of the five inhabited continents (with the Americas counting as one continents).\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the meaning\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 857}, {\"ngram\": \"the rings\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 870}, {\"ngram\": \"their five individual colours\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 904}, {\"ngram\": \"the five inhabited continents\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 953}, {\"ngram\": \"the Americas counting\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 981}, {\"ngram\": \"one continents\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 999}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And while that may be true of today's interpretation, it wasn't Coubertin's original message.\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1095, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"today's interpretation\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1054}, {\"ngram\": \"Coubertin's original message\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1094}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the six colours (blue, black, green, yellow, red and the white of the Olympic flag) represtented every colour that appeared on the flags of those nations participating in the Olympics at the time.\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1302, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the six colours\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1121}, {\"ngram\": \"the white\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1168}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic flag\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1188}, {\"ngram\": \"every colour\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"the flags\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1242}, {\"ngram\": \"those nations\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1259}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1289}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1293, \"to\": 1301}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This ensured every nation was represented in the symbol, competing under one banner and with unity at the forefront of the Games' purpose.\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1441, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every nation\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1328}, {\"ngram\": \"the symbol\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1358}, {\"ngram\": \"one banner\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1386}, {\"ngram\": \"unity\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"the forefront\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1418}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games' purpose\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The six colours [including the flag's white background] combined in this way reproduce the colours of every country without exception,\\\" Coubertin explained in the August 1913 edition of Olympique.\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1640, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The six colours\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1459}, {\"ngram\": \"the flag's white background\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1498}, {\"ngram\": \"this way\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1520}, {\"ngram\": \"the colours\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1542}, {\"ngram\": \"every country\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1559}, {\"ngram\": \"exception\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1577}, {\"ngram\": \"Coubertin\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1589}, {\"ngram\": \"the August 1913 edition\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1626}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympique\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1639}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The blue and yellow of Sweden, the blue and white of Greece, the tricolour flags of France, United Kingdom, the United States, Germany, Belgium, Italy and Hungary, and the yellow and red of Spain are included, as are the innovative flags of Brazil and Australia, and those of ancient Japan and modern China.\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1949, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1665, \"end\": 1671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"score\": 0.9578834973510257, \"rank\": 0.043959071216954214, \"text\": \"Sweden\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\"}, {\"begin\": 1695, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9673393884736841, \"rank\": 0.0335657950283456, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1726, \"end\": 1732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9906927080271076, \"rank\": 0.008127203942491395, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1734, \"end\": 1748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.999999318776877, \"rank\": 6.46591547673991e-07, \"text\": \"United Kingdom\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1754, \"end\": 1767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uni